qutebrowser Adblocking Support\n\nSince version 2.0.0, if the Python adblock library is available, qutebrowser will use it to integrate Brave's Rust adblocker library for improved adblocking, based on ABP-like filter lists (such as EasyList).\n\n## Configuring Filter Lists\n\nYou can add URLs to ABP-style adblocking rulesets through the content.blocking.adblock.lists setting, with an overview of available lists available at https://adblockplus.org/en/subscriptions.\n\n## Regarding Japanese Adblock Filters\n\nWhile my search results don't contain specific information about Japanese-language adblock filter lists for qutebrowser as of 2025, the general approach would be to:\n\n1. Run :adblock-update to download adblock lists and activate adblocking.\n2. Add the Japanese filter list URLs to your qutebrowser configuration's `content.blocking.adblock.lists` setting if you find appropriate Japanese ad-blocking filter lists.\n\nTo find specific Japanese adblock filter lists, you would want to search the Adblock Plus subscriptions directory or look for community-maintained Japanese-language filter lists that use the ABP (Adblock Plus) format.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"60b0f7e5-f67a-4314-a041-2ce196a0d1ed","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:25:51.941Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"qutebrowser japanese adblock filter list 2025 日本語 広告ブロック フィルター","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01CCUjSVEbfJ4HWPP9wf1sbe","content":[{"title":"Frequently asked questions | qutebrowser","url":"https://qutebrowser.org/FAQ.html"},{"title":"adblock logger · qutebrowser/qutebrowser · Discussion #8272","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/discussions/8272"},{"title":"adblock: Support cosmetic filtering (element hiding) and scriptlets · Issue #6480 · qutebrowser/qutebrowser","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/issues/6480"},{"title":"More sophisticated adblocking · Issue #29 · qutebrowser/qutebrowser","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/issues/29"},{"title":"qutebrowser - ArchWiki","url":"https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Qutebrowser"},{"title":"Unable to update adblock · Issue #7172 · qutebrowser/qutebrowser","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/issues/7172"},{"title":"qutebrowser quickstart | qutebrowser","url":"https://qutebrowser.org/doc/quickstart.html"},{"title":"adblock format · qutebrowser/qutebrowser · Discussion #6089","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/discussions/6089"},{"title":"| qutebrowser","url":"https://www.qutebrowser.org/doc/help/settings.html"},{"title":"Slower startup with host adblock list · Issue #7920 · qutebrowser/qutebrowser","url":"https://github.com/qutebrowser/qutebrowser/issues/7920"}]},"Based on my search results, here's what I found about qutebrowser and adblock filter lists:\n\n## qutebrowser Adblocking Support\n\nSince version 2.0.0, if the Python adblock library is available, qutebrowser will use it to integrate Brave's Rust adblocker library for improved adblocking, based on ABP-like filter lists (such as EasyList).\n\n## Configuring Filter Lists\n\nYou can add URLs to ABP-style adblocking rulesets through the content.blocking.adblock.lists setting, with an overview of available lists available at https://adblockplus.org/en/subscriptions.\n\n## Regarding Japanese Adblock Filters\n\nWhile my search results don't contain specific information about Japanese-language adblock filter lists for qutebrowser as of 2025, the general approach would be to:\n\n1. Run :adblock-update to download adblock lists and activate adblocking.\n2. Add the Japanese filter list URLs to your qutebrowser configuration's `content.blocking.adblock.lists` setting if you find appropriate Japanese ad-blocking filter lists.\n\nTo find specific Japanese adblock filter lists, you would want to search the Adblock Plus subscriptions directory or look for community-maintained Japanese-language filter lists that use the ABP (Adblock Plus) format."],"durationSeconds":6.688485100000049},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"f02210ec-5336-4919-baa5-cd0579b24c84"}
